{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon",

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Multi-agent system for airline policy inquiries using real-time web scraping via webpage_rag. Scrapes the airline's FAQ and main site pages at runtime to answer customer questions about baggage, fares, travel planning, and special services.",
        "tags": ["AAOSA", "customer-service", "airline", "policy-management", "web-scraping", "RAG", "tool"]
        "sample_queries": [
            "What are the bag size and weight limits on this airline?",
            "My checked bag was delayed, what should I do?",
            "What ID do I need to fly?",
            "Can I bring my pet on a flight?",
            "Does the airline offer wheelchair assistance?",
        ]
    },

    include "config/llm_config.hocon",

    "instructions_prefix": """
- **Lead with a direct, clear answer** to the customer's question first.
- **NEVER OMIT** RELEVANT conditions, restrictions, variations, exceptions, qualifications — including fees, pricing tiers, and every step of any multi-step procedure.
- **NEVER use external knowledge**. Base every answer strictly on information retrieved from the tool. If information is unavailable, say so explicitly.
- **NEVER PARAPHRASE POLICY TEXT**. Do NOT use quotes. Do NOT include a section titled anything like "Variations, ..."
- The RAG tool returns document chunks. Each chunk contains a "metadata" field with a "source" key holding the page URL. Extract that URL and include it at the end of your reply as "Source URL: <url>".
- ONLY include URLs mentioned by your tool.
""",

    "tools": [
        {
            "name": "Airline_Policy_Agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
                Handles all customer questions about airline policies, procedures, and services and provides source links.
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "query": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
A customer question about airline policies, procedures, or services that may require web search to retrieve up-to-date information and source links.
"""
                        },
                    },
                    "required": ["query"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """
            You are the top-level airline policy inquiry agent and the sole point of interaction with the customer.
            DO NOT mention other tools, agents, or internal systems. NEVER treat retrieved information as belonging to a different airline.
            NEVER ask the customer which airline they are asking about — all questions refer to this airline.
            Only answer questions within your scope — airline policies, procedures, and helpdesk inquiries — and politely decline any unrelated questions.

            You route customer queries to topic-specific agents and compose a single answer. Follow these steps:
            1. DECOMPOSE — Break the user query into simpler sub-questions.
            2. ROUTE — For each sub-question, identify the one agent whose description best matches that topic and call that agent with only that sub-question.
               Do NOT call agents whose scope is completely unrelated to the sub-question. If no agent applies to a sub-question, note that it is out of scope.
            Example: "I'm traveling with my lap infant, ID requirements for my infant and a stroller. What do I need to know?" becomes:
                 (a) "Information about traveling with a lap infant?" routed to agent: Kids_and_Pets
                 (b) "Information about traveling with strollers?" routed to agent: Kids_and_Pets
                 (c) "Information about ID requirements for infants?" routed to agent: Travel_Documents
            3. COMPOSE — Build a unified answer from all agent responses.
            4. SOURCES — At the end of your answer, list all "Source:" URLs from the agents you used under a **Sources:** header. Include one URL per line. Do not duplicate URLs.
            Filter out URLs from agents whose answers you did not use. ONLY include URLs explicitly mentioned by the sub-agents.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Optional_Services_Pricing", "Bag_Count_Restrictions", "Bag_Delayed", "Bag_Damaged", "Bag_Missing_Items", "Sporting_Musical_Equipment",
            "Firearms_Policy", "Smart_Luggage", "Bundle_Differences", "Seating_Options", "Food_And_Beverages", "Miles_And_Points", "Elite_Status_Benefits",
            "Military_Benefits", "Travel_Documents", "Restricted_Items", "Kids_and_Pets", "Accessibility"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Optional_Services_Pricing",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to pricing for optional services including:
                - Baggage: size/weight limits, carry-on fees, checked bag fees, overweight and oversized fees
                - Booking extras: care agent, name change, GoWild, Discount Den, agent assistance
                - Premium services: Flight Flexibility, Board First, Priority Boarding, Web Check-in
                - Other services: pet charges, carrier interface fees, flight modification fees,
                  cancellation fees, and other optional services
                Does not cover bag count limits, baggage issues, or bundle specifications.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Optional_Services_Pricing agent. You handle pricing for optional services: baggage fees, booking extras, premium services, and other charges.
            Always call your Optional_Services_Pricing_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Optional_Services_Pricing_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Bag_Count_Restrictions",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to the maximum number of carry-on, personal item, and checked bags
                a passenger is allowed to bring. Does not cover bag sizes, weight limits, fees, or pricing.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Bag_Count_Restrictions agent. You handle how many carry-on, personal item, and checked bags a passenger can bring.
            Always call your Bag_Count_Restrictions_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Bag_Count_Restrictions_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Bag_Delayed",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to delayed or missing checked bag claims, tracking, and resolution procedures.
                Does not cover damaged bags or missing items inside bags.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Bag_Delayed agent. You handle delayed or missing checked bag claims, tracking, and resolution.
            Always call your Bag_Delayed_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Bag_Delayed_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Bag_Damaged",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to damaged checked bag claims and what qualifies as damaged.
                Does not cover delayed bags or missing items inside bags.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Bag_Damaged agent. You handle damaged checked bag claims and what qualifies as damage.
            Always call your Bag_Damaged_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Bag_Damaged_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Bag_Missing_Items",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to items found missing from inside a checked bag after a flight,
                or items left on the aircraft or at the airport. Does not cover delayed, missing, or damaged bags.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Bag_Missing_Items agent. You handle items missing from inside a checked bag or left on the aircraft or at the airport.
            Always call your Bag_Missing_Items_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Bag_Missing_Items_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Sporting_Musical_Equipment",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to traveling with sporting equipment and musical instruments.
                Does not cover firearms or smart luggage.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Sporting_Musical_Equipment agent. You handle policies for traveling with sporting equipment and musical instruments.
            Always call your Sporting_Musical_Equipment_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Sporting_Musical_Equipment_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Firearms_Policy",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to all rules, restrictions, and fees for traveling with firearms and ammunition.
                Does not cover sporting equipment or smart luggage.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Firearms_Policy agent. You handle rules, restrictions, and fees for traveling with firearms and ammunition.
            Always call your Firearms_Policy_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Firearms_Policy_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Smart_Luggage",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to all rules, restrictions, and fees for traveling with smart luggage
                containing lithium batteries. Does not cover sporting equipment or firearms.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Smart_Luggage agent. You handle rules, restrictions, and fees for traveling with smart luggage containing lithium batteries.
            Always call your Smart_Luggage_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Smart_Luggage_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Bundle_Differences",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to the differences between Economy, Premium, and Business bundles
                and what each bundle includes. Does not cover base fare, upgrades, or anything else without a bundle.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Bundle_Differences agent. You handle differences between Economy, Premium, and Business bundles and what each includes.
            Always call your Bundle_Differences_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Bundle_Differences_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Seating_Options",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to seat categories (First, UpFront Plus, Premium, Preferred, and Standard),
                seat selection during booking and check-in, free seat upgrades for elite status members,
                and family seating for children 13 and under.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Seating_Options agent. You handle seat categories, seat selection, elite seat upgrades, and family seating.
            Always call your Seating_Options_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Seating_Options_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Food_And_Beverages",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to in-flight food and beverage availability.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Food_And_Beverages agent. You handle in-flight food and beverage availability.
            Always call your Food_And_Beverages_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Food_And_Beverages_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Miles_And_Points",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to how Frontier miles and points are earned: earning rates per dollar spent,
                FRONTIER Airlines World Mastercard earnings, and mileage partner earnings.
                Does not cover elite status benefits or travel perks.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Miles_And_Points agent. You handle how Frontier miles and points are earned: spending, credit card, and mileage partners.
            Always call your Miles_And_Points_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Miles_And_Points_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Elite_Status_Benefits",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to Elite Status tiers (Silver, Gold, Platinum, Diamond) and their travel benefits:
                qualifications, boarding priority, complimentary bags, seat upgrades, mileage multiplier earnings,
                no change/cancel fees, family pooling, Discount Den discounts, gold/silver status pass, companion travel,
                pet fee waivers, and refundability. Does not cover how to earn miles or military-specific benefits.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Elite_Status_Benefits agent. You handle Elite Status tiers (Silver, Gold, Platinum, Diamond) and their travel benefits.
            Always call your Elite_Status_Benefits_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Elite_Status_Benefits_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Military_Benefits",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to travel benefits for active U.S. military personnel and their accompanying
                spouse and children, including qualifications, complimentary bags and overweight/oversize fee waivers,
                eligibility requirements, and how to add military bags.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Military_Benefits agent. You handle travel benefits for active U.S. military personnel and their accompanying family.
            Always call your Military_Benefits_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Military_Benefits_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Travel_Documents",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to accepted forms of ID (REAL ID) and travel document requirements for domestic
                and international travel, children and permanent residents. Does not cover TSA prohibited items
                or what passengers may pack.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Travel_Documents agent. You handle accepted forms of ID and travel document requirements for domestic and international travel.
            Always call your Travel_Documents_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Travel_Documents_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Restricted_Items",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to TSA allowed and prohibited items in carry-on and checked bags,
                including liquids (3-1-1 rule), sharp objects, food, and other TSA-regulated items.
                Does not cover firearms or other special baggage (which have their own policies).
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Restricted_Items agent. You handle TSA allowed and prohibited items in carry-on and checked bags.
            Always call your Restricted_Items_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Restricted_Items_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Kids_and_Pets",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to traveling with children and pets: lap infants, family seating, strollers,
                car seats, formula and baby items in carry-on, adding a child to a reservation, infant boarding
                passes, traveling while pregnant, nursing, and allowed pet species and their requirements and fees.
                Does not cover service animals.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Kids_and_Pets agent. You handle traveling with children and pets: lap infants, family seating, strollers, car seats, and pet policies.
            Call your Kids_and_Pets_RAG tool once per distinct topic in the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Kids_and_Pets_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Accessibility",
            "function": ${aaosa_call}{
                "description": """
                Handles queries related to accessibility and special services: wheelchair availability and airport
                assistance, manual and electric mobility devices and damage claims, portable oxygen concentrators,
                medicine and medical devices in carry-on, service animals, accommodations for deaf and blind
                passengers, nut and food allergy policies, safety and personal care assistants, airport agent
                assistance, extra seat space, unaccompanied minors, human remains policy, and adding or modifying
                special service requests.
                """
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
            You are the Accessibility agent. You handle accessibility and special services: wheelchairs, mobility devices, oxygen, medical devices, service animals, allergies, and accommodations.
            Always call your Accessibility_RAG tool with the user's query. Answer ONLY based on the retrieved information.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},
            "tools": ["Accessibility_RAG"]
        },

        {
            "name": "Optional_Services_Pricing_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://www.flyfrontier.com/optional-services/"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Bag_Count_Restrictions_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/are-there-any-restrictions-on-how-many-bags-i-can-bring"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Bag_Delayed_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/bags-delayed-damage-and-missing-items-my-bag-is-delayed-who-can-i-talk-to"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Bag_Damaged_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/bags-delayed-damage-and-missing-items-my-bag-has-been-damaged-what-should-i-do"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Bag_Missing_Items_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/what-do-i-do-if-an-item-is-missing-in-my-checked-bag"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Sporting_Musical_Equipment_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/bags-seats-general-info-can-i-bring-sporting-or-musical-equipment-with-me"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Firearms_Policy_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/bags-seats-general-info-can-i-bring-a-firearm-with-me"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Smart_Luggage_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/can-i-bring-smart-luggage-on-my-flight"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Bundle_Differences_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/what-is-the-difference-between-economy-premium-and-business-bundles"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Seating_Options_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://www.flyfrontier.com/travel-information/seating-options"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Food_And_Beverages_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/do-you-offer-complimentary-food-and-beverages-in-flight"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Miles_And_Points_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/how-are-frontier-miles-and-points-earned"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Elite_Status_Benefits_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/what-travel-benefits-are-included-with-elite-status"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Military_Benefits_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/military-personnel-bags"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Travel_Documents_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/what-identification-or-documents-do-i-need-in-order-to-travel"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Restricted_Items_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/what-does-tsa-allow-and-not-allow-on-flights"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Kids_and_Pets_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/traveling-with-children-or-pets"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Accessibility_RAG",
            "toolbox": "webpage_rag",
            "args": {
                "urls": ["https://faq.flyfrontier.com/help/special-services"]
            }
        },
    ]
}
